# Walshard Studio — Licensing Overview

Copyright (c) 2026 Vlad Cioaba.
Upstream repository: https://github.com/vladcioaba/walshardstudio

This repository is governed by **three** licenses, depending on which
directory a file lives in. Pick the one that matches what you are doing.

---

## Mission

Walshard Studio is intended to remain a **free-of-charge tool for the
community in perpetuity**. Anyone may use it for personal projects,
study, education, charity, and hobby work without payment, and may
modify it and share their modifications under the same terms.

**Nobody may monetize the editor itself except the original author
(Vlad Cioaba).** This is a deliberate, permanent design choice — not
an oversight. The license terms below enforce it. If you want to use
the editor commercially in a way the license does not already permit,
contact the original author for a separate written commercial
license.

---

## 1. Editor source — PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0

**Applies to everything in this repository EXCEPT the subtrees listed in
sections 2 and 3 below.** This covers:

* `app/**` (including `app/UILayoutEditor/**`, the editor library)
* `proj.ios_mac/**`
* `tools/**`
* `tests/**`
* `CMakeLists.txt` and build scripts
* All documentation in this repo

You may use, copy, study, modify, and distribute the editor source **for
any noncommercial purpose**. You may NOT (this list is illustrative,
not exhaustive — the controlling rule is the Reservation of Commercial
Rights below):

* Sell the editor, a fork of it, or a derivative of it, in source or
  binary form
* Offer the editor (or any fork or derivative) as a paid hosted
  service, SaaS, cloud product, or on-demand build service
* Bundle the editor (or any fork or derivative) into a paid product,
  paid bundle, paid asset pack, paid course, or paid training program
* Charge any fee, subscription, royalty, or other consideration for
  installations, downloads, mirrors, distributions, or access to the
  editor or any fork or derivative
* Accept paid sponsorships, advertising revenue, or paid placements
  embedded in a fork's user interface or distribution channel
* Distribute any fork without retaining the upstream copyright notice
  and a reference to the upstream repository URL above

A "noncommercial purpose" is defined by the PolyForm Noncommercial
License 1.0.0, reproduced in full at the bottom of this file. Notably,
use by individuals for hobby projects, study, and personal entertainment
is permitted; use by charitable, educational, and public research
organizations is permitted regardless of funding.

**Required Notice** (must accompany any redistribution of editor
source under PolyForm NC):

> Required Notice: Copyright (c) 2026 Vlad Cioaba.
> Source: https://github.com/vladcioaba/walshardstudio

### Reservation of Commercial Rights

As the sole copyright holder of the editor source covered by this
Section 1, **Vlad Cioaba reserves all rights to commercial
exploitation of that source in perpetuity, exclusively to himself.**

No license granted by this repository to any other person — under
PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0, under the Upstream Integration Grant,
or otherwise — conveys any commercial right in the editor source to
any other party. In particular, no forker, sub-licensee, downstream
recipient, or contributor acquires any right to:

1. Sell, rent, lease, sublicense for a fee, or otherwise charge for
   copies of the editor (in source or binary form)
2. Operate the editor (or a fork or derivative) as a paid service of
   any kind, including SaaS, hosted, cloud, on-demand, or
   build-as-a-service offerings
3. Bundle the editor (or a fork or derivative) into any product,
   subscription, course, training program, asset pack, or
   distribution that is sold, licensed for a fee, or accessed in
   exchange for any consideration
4. Receive paid sponsorships, advertising revenue, paid placements,
   or any other commercial consideration tied to the editor or a
   fork's branding, distribution, or user interface

These reserved rights remain reserved through every level of forking
and sub-distribution. Acquiring a copy of the editor from a forker
(rather than directly from the original repository) does not enlarge
the rights you receive — your rights flow directly from the original
licensor under the terms in this file, and the original licensor's
reservation of commercial rights binds you regardless of what any
intermediate forker may have purported to grant.

This reservation is **independent of, and in addition to**, the
restrictions in PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0. Where the two overlap,
the more restrictive applies. Where PolyForm NC permits something
that the Reservation of Commercial Rights forbids, the reservation
controls.

The original licensor may, by separate signed written agreement and
on a case-by-case basis, grant a paid commercial license to any
person who wishes to exercise a reserved commercial right. No such
agreement is granted or implied by this repository's license text;
contact the original author to negotiate one.

The original licensor may also, at his sole discretion, transfer or
delegate the reserved commercial rights to a successor entity
(including but not limited to a company he forms or controls). Any
such successor inherits the reservation in its entirety; the
reservation never lapses into the public domain.

