## Source Attribution requirement (Section 1 only)

Any fork or derivative work covered by Section 1 must retain a clearly
visible reference to the upstream repository in **all** of:

1. The README (or equivalent top-level documentation) of the fork
2. The "About" dialog or equivalent in the running application
3. Source files that already carry an upstream copyright notice — do
   not strip those headers

This is in addition to PolyForm Noncommercial's own "Notices" clause,
which already requires the Required Notice above to travel with the
software.

