## Upstream Integration Grant (applies to Sections 1 and 2)

By forking, modifying, or otherwise creating a derivative work of any
file covered by Section 1 (PolyForm Noncommercial editor source) or
Section 2 (MIT runtime library), you grant **the original licensor
(Vlad Cioaba) and any successor maintainer of the upstream repository
at the URL named at the top of this file** a **perpetual, worldwide,
non-exclusive, royalty-free, irrevocable license** to:

1. Copy any portion of your modifications back into the upstream
   Walshard Studio repository, and
2. Re-license those modifications under the same license that governs
   the file they are integrated into (PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0 for
   Section 1 files, or MIT for Section 2 files), and
3. Distribute, sublicense, and otherwise exercise all rights granted by
   that license over the integrated modifications.

You further agree that, on request from the Walshard Studio
maintainers, you will identify modifications you have made to the
software and the location where they are published, so that the
maintainers may evaluate them for upstream integration. You retain all
copyright in your modifications; this grant is a license, not an
assignment.

This clause exists so that improvements developed in forks can flow
back into the upstream project without each contributor needing to
sign a separate CLA. It does not require you to make your fork public
or to push changes upstream — only that, if and when the maintainers
ask, you allow your modifications to be integrated under the same
license terms that already cover the rest of the file.

